# Brand Media System Reference

This project ships **tenant-specific brand assets** (logos, wordmarks, card art, error states) synced from Airtable ("All Media"). Unlike icons or illustrations, media is **branded** — each asset belongs to a single tenant. The pipeline emits one self-contained module per tenant with inherited parent assets pre-merged.

## Tenants & Inheritance

Tenants form a small inheritance tree. Each tenant's manifest entry and runtime barrel contain its **fully merged** asset set — parent assets plus the tenant's own overrides — so consumers never have to walk the chain themselves.

| Tenant key | Label | Inherits from |
|------------|-------|----------------|
| `wcp` | WCP | — (root for Walmart family) |
| `walmart-business` | Walmart Business | `wcp` |
| `walmart-legacy` | Walmart Legacy | `wcp` |
| `walmart-mx` | Walmart MX | `wcp` |
| `walmart-ca` | Walmart CA | `wcp` |
| `walmart-plus` | Walmart+ | `wcp` |
| `sams-club` | Sam's Club | `wcp` |
| `sams-club-maverick` | Sam's Club Maverick | `sams-club` |
| `members-mark` | Member's Mark | `sams-club` |
| `bodega` | Bodega | `wcp` |

`getMedia('walmart-business', 'LogoSpark')` returns the WCP default unless `walmart-business` has its own override — no manual fallback needed at the call site.

## Theme ↔ Tenant Mapping

The active theme resolves to exactly one most-specific tenant. Use the helper rather than hardcoding:

```tsx
import {
  getMediaTenantForTheme,
  useThemeMediaTenant,
  THEME_MEDIA_TENANT,
} from '{{ld_root_path}}/utils/mediaManager';

// Imperative (with a known theme name)
getMediaTenantForTheme('Walmart');         // 'wcp'
getMediaTenantForTheme('Walmart B2B');     // 'walmart-business'
getMediaTenantForTheme('Walmart Legacy');  // 'walmart-legacy'
getMediaTenantForTheme("Sam's Club");      // 'sams-club'
getMediaTenantForTheme("Member's Mark");   // 'members-mark'

// React hook (subscribes to theme changes)
const tenant = useThemeMediaTenant();      // most-specific tenant key
```

The full mapping lives in `THEME_MEDIA_TENANT`. The legacy hook `useThemeMediaKey()` is also re-exported but returns the **coarse** 3-bucket key (`wcp` | `sams-club` | `bodega`); prefer `useThemeMediaTenant()` in new code.

## How to Find Available Media

1. **Programmatic** — use the helpers below (preferred for code).
2. **Manifest** — read `src/media/manifest.json`. Top level keys are tenants; each entry has `label`, `count`, and `assets: [{name, token, kind, width, height}]`.
3. **Review page** — open `#media-<tenant>` in the running app (e.g. `#media-walmart-business`, `#media-members-mark`).

## Asset Kinds

Each asset has a `kind`:

| Kind | Stored as | How to render |
|------|-----------|---------------|
| `svg` | Inline SVG markup string | `<span dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{__html: svg}} />` |
| `png` | `data:image/png;base64,…` URL | `<img src={src} alt="…" />` |

## Programmatic Access

All media code should import from `src/utils/mediaManager`:

```tsx
import {
  getMedia,
  listMedia,
  hasMedia,
  searchMedia,
  listTenants,
  getTenantInfo,
  getMediaToken,
  getMediaTenantForTheme,
  useThemeMediaTenant,
  THEME_MEDIA_TENANT,
} from '{{ld_root_path}}/utils/mediaManager';

// Discovery
const tenants = listTenants();              // 10 tenant keys
const info = getTenantInfo('walmart-business'); // { label: 'Walmart Business', count: N }
const all = listMedia('sams-club');         // MediaAsset[] (merged set, includes inherited wcp assets)
const exists = hasMedia('walmart-plus', 'LogoSpark'); // true (inherited from wcp)
const matches = searchMedia('wcp', 'logo'); // names containing "logo"

// Lookup — returns null if name is unknown for the tenant
const asset = getMedia('walmart-business', 'LogoSpark');
if (asset?.kind === 'svg') {
  // <span dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{__html: asset.svg}} />
} else if (asset?.kind === 'png') {
  // <img src={asset.src} width={asset.width} height={asset.height} alt="…" />
}

// Token (Airtable design-token name, e.g. for documentation)
const token = getMediaToken('wcp', 'LogoSpark');
```

## Common Asset Categories

Names follow PascalCase. Typical categories present across tenants (use `listMedia(tenant)` for the full list):

- **Logos & wordmarks** — `LogoSpark`, `LogoWordmark`, `LogoMonochrome`, brand glyphs
- **Card art** — `CreditCardBrand`, `CreditCardBrand1`…N (Walmart-family payment cards)
- **Error states** — graphics for 404, empty-cart, no-results, offline
- **Marketing marks** — seasonal, campaign, partner co-branding

## Rules

- **Don't hand-edit** `src/media/*` — these are generated by `npm run airtable:pull-media`. Hand edits get overwritten on the next sync.
- **Check the active theme** before using tenant-specific assets — use `getMediaTenantForTheme(theme)` or `useThemeMediaTenant()` so the right tenant (with the right brand overrides) is picked automatically. Inheritance means an inherited `LogoSpark` will resolve even on tenants that don't define their own, so consumers don't need fallback chains.
- **Branch on `kind`** when rendering — SVG and PNG render differently.
- **Accessibility**: provide an `alt` (for `<img>`) or wrap SVG markup in a `<span role="img" aria-label="…">`. Pass empty string for purely decorative usage and mark `aria-hidden`.
